'd move the table and go out, you could go out, but oh no, not us. But we never did - he wouldn't let us disturb - other people, you know what I mean? Now he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
Would your mum serve food to whoever came in next or did she have a special order for serving people, did your dad get his first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
Oh - me dad used to get his. But he wouldn't have it if anybody was in. My - outsiders, no. No, he's - very funny. Then perhaps me mother'd have a good hiding after for that. Every week. Me mother's had a black 
eye. I mean we used to love me father just the same. That's what they call love in them days, I don't know what they'd call it now I'm sure. Do you know - he's never picked his hand up to me - in the forty-two years as I've been married to him. Me first d
idn't. He did it other ways. Well - him, he wouldn't. He'd say, what? If you can afford it you have it. I'll bring it. But when you know how much money you've got coming in how, see. But I'd rather have - this life - than I would the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Would you describe your mum as an easy person to talk to?
