ll there were - nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 So the family never went away for a holiday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
Can you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days? You sound as if you spent them at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Oh - yes, that's what I did do. Running errands. Borrowing money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Now how about Sundays, would you go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
Sundays - no. We didn't, No. He got - me father had got sisters as used to go to - Bedford chapel, Sunday - mornings and Sunday nights, regular as clockwork, and my father stood on 
the front steps smoking his pipe, waiting for 'em to come down, and they always went Hanley cemetery after they come out of chapel - chapel it was, and - we daresn't show our face through the door. Oh no. And - used to beckon me father - to the end of the
 
street, and - our Fred this and Fred the other, that's how they used to talk to me father, and - me father - you know, well - used to have more manners then when he was talking to them than he did - any other time. Soon as they give him money he used to g
et himself washed and - dressed, mind you he'd got clothes to go out in, but - he never went nowhere, only the pub. The Bridge Inn. He never went gadding off. No. I never knew - knew him to - to go out - same as they do you - now you know, no, he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 He sort of stuck around home really?
