now your name? No, I said, she never - she knows me first name. Florrie. That's all. Right. You're not going to more. I'll let that woman down. Yes. To think, he said, as I'm working on Twyfords, he says, fireman, and me mother was there and you - oh God 
he says. You're not going no more. And that was that. I thought oh dear - what next. Well - kept getting these bits of jobs you know and - and then in the finish - after I left school and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 What other kinds of jobs would have then apart from the bread 
delivering job and bits of cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
Oh I - I used to do a lot of cleaning up at home. You know, after - oh I never - were cleaning, only - when it was when I was married to me first husband, and I was expecting me first child. And I cleaned for this
 woman where I had what you call trust. And - oh I could clean, I was like as strong as a horse you know. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
So the part time jobs you got when you were still at school, you got them off your own initiative?
