\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 What hours did you work when you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Same. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Five and a half days a week again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Did you get more money when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
Oh yes. We had about - two pound ten to three pound a week. It was good money you know. It was, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Why did they pay you so well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
Well it was - the work, you see. It was dangerous you know. If you got any of that on your chest. Well if I'd have stuck that another twelvemonth after I'd had - before I had the baby - oh perhaps I wouldn't have been here today. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
So you got paid the money really because you were running the risk of getting diseases?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Yes. Yes. Yes, it was good money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
So this was a much more decent wage but in fact you were running danger to get it weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 What happened to this wage, did you hand all that over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
Oh I had to do, yes, else me father'd have gone down and enquired. And if I'd have said - you know, this - I got this job before I got married you see, to me first husband, and 
if he'd have found out as I was getting - you know - well - the money as I was getting I was turning up, if he thought - if he'd have thought as I was keeping any out of it - I'd have got it. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Did they give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 A shilling a week. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Did you like this work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
Yes I did. Yes, I was fond of it. There was girls - just the men - as belonged to the machines, and - the women. You see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 So really these two jobs, the paper cutting and the one at the Cromo, the
se were the only two jobs you had up to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
That's right. And then I went to work - oh I went to work at the wagon works.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
Well - would it be when the war was on then? You know, when I worked - worked at the wagon works. I know our Arthur was only a bit of a lad then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 What were you doing there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Oh - I was on a - ay? I didn't. I did not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 What did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 On a boring machine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 No, haven't got nothing do on the boring machi
ne, we used to have to go - round the the shops were the wagons were and pick screws up, nuts - straighten the place up, you know. Yes, I - I - I worked on the boarding machine - oh for a good while. And then I used - when we'd got nothing else to do - so
l
bas I used to - make - agains the holes you know, and - take so much - of the wood out, see, it was oak. And - then when we'd finished that, me and this other girl used to - go down the shavings - hole - when they'd finished, putting planks - wood through
 the - the machine they used to - we used to go down and bag these - they'd say to us - the old man had easy They keep out of the road, go down the shavings hole. Oh, it would be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Was that the last job you had outside the home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Yes. That was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 So since then you've been a housewife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
And - oh I was single, I wasn't married then, when I got that. And - a woman - well I saw - I saw her this year - and I couldn't believe me own eyes, and it was the woman as used to - go to work with me,
 used to call our house every morning after the - perhaps a cup of tea you know and - we've gone - down to the works, 'cos it was on - not many - many yards you know. And then Twyfords.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 After you had worked at the wagon works then did you go back to Cromo?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 No. Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
I thought you said you were working at the Cromo when you had your first child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Yes I was. Oh it must have been - after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 So the wagon works must have come after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 No, the wagon works I - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 When you left school in 1912 you went as paper cutter for a few weeks?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Then you went to Johnsons }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15404464\charrsid10703177 Potbank}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Where you worked in the dipping room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 Dipping house. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 You worked there for about twelve months? Then you went to t
he wagon works and you were there for about four years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
It was in 1918 in fact you went to work for the Cromo and you stayed there until your daughter was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 That's right. Yes, that - you've got it right there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10306935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 T
hat in fact was the last job you had because you became a housewife after that when you had the two children? Would you have preferred another type of job, were you happy with these jobs that you got or was there anything you would have preferred to have 
done had you had an open choice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5664013 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16718425\charrsid10703177 
Well I'd got no - I'd got no option - really. Me brother - he was working at the wagon works, and - he said to me, he says, Lol, he says - you can get a job, he says down at the wagon works where I work. I said, what w
ould I do, I said, I can't - what, climbing in and out wagons? No, he says. You'd perhaps get a job - on a boring machine and filling bags with - shavings and - odd jobs. He said, well any road, he says, come down in the morning. So I went down. But - me 
a
nd this woman and I know, and she lives next door to me sisters - and I never saw her - after we left the wagon works until then. Oh - and - she knew me straight away. But believe me I couldn't tell her. She'd got very long black hair and she'd got it in 
t
wo plaits. Never had her hair no different. And it was hanging down - it was right down here. Beautiful hair she'd got. And she was on the poor side you know. Well - I felt sorry for her and - I used to - it was only me and her, we used to talk to the men
 
you know how they are, and we used to go on the - makings, on the sidings and empty wagons, oh in the frosty weather. Oh aye we did. But - every week we had a - a - so much money, but we didn't know this - at all, for emptying these wagons on the rail roa
d
. On the sidings. Well this money was put into the - well - well I suppose on on the works you know. Oh I'd been - I'd been left a good while, me and this - and they was Victoria Brammer. And oh she was - she was nice you know. And - we never mixed with '
e
m - with anybody. There was women - women, so many women working there. But me and her were always the same, you know. But her was come day go day, you know. And - she got a little boy, she weren't married, and she'd got one little boy like curly hair and
 
she got to work and keep - this child. And I think that's the reason as I felt sorry for her. But - after I'd left there - oh I got the job as easy as anything. And - the chap as worked - this machine, I had to go on this machine, and he was a sergeant in
 the army. Yes, I'll never forget it. And we - I had a - a - a young fellow as I was writing to. 'Course me mother knew this and me father knew. Oh they didn't stop me, not then, and - I was - keeping in touch with him sort of thing, but he was in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}France{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. W
ell this sergeant as I was doing this work - on this machine, it was his job, and he said to me, he says - you're on my job. I said, am I on your job, I said, when you've got a job to do in the army? 'Cos he was in uniform. And - he says - well it is my j
o
b. I said, well you're welcome to it, I said, if you come home. I said, it's no - I said, it's no easy pie, I said, on here. It wasn't you know, it was hard work. And - you know the size of wagons don't you? The size of 'em? Them were solbars. And the bac
