 - and the front - were headstocks oh yes. And you got every hole - direct, you've got to have it direct, and I got use a machine you see. So of course - we were talking and he - he asked me to meet him. Well, which I did. And I was writing to this other 
- this other fellow. And he didn't know, 'cos I didn't let on to him, well it was nothing to do with him. So any road, we had our photographs taken. I never saw 'em. But we had our photograph taken at the - where was {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}
}Strand{\*\xmlclose}, in Piccadilly. I never saw these
 photographs but - I went out with him nearly a week. Oh me mother let me - oh me mother let me go. Yes. And I don't know why, but her did. And - well when he got back - he was a sergeant over this - Tom as I was writing to, and he lived next door to him.
 
It's true. I never - I never heard - a line - well I didn't hear nothing, he - he was gone. Had this sergeant. And - but any road, Tom when he wrote to me - he - he asked for his belongings. I said to me mother, I said, what belongings does he want? I sai
d
, the cards he's sent you. And his - badges you know as they used to put on their hats and all that. Oh, I said, I - I'm not going to send 'em, I said, if - if he wants 'em he must come and fetch 'em. You know. But I never saw him - 'til long after the wa
